Kenny Motsamai File picture: Simphiwe Nkwali Former Pan Africanist Congress prisoner Kenny Motsamai has been released after spending 28 years in prison eNCA reported. Motsamai was a PAC prisoner arrested in 1989 for the murder of a traffic officer during a bank robbery which was sanctioned by the party. The robberies were used to fund PAC activities. Motsamai has been on day parole for the past seven months meaning he can be out of prison during the day with an electronic tracking device but has to return to prison at night. Related Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share